        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 2:06PM CDT until July 24 at 3:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>SVRLOT

The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Kendall County in northeastern Illinois...
Northeastern La Salle County in north central Illinois...
Southeastern De Kalb County in north central Illinois...
Southern Kane County in northeastern Illinois...

* Until 300 PM CDT.

* At 205 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Hinckley to near Leland, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Severe thunderstorms will be near...
Sugar Grove, Lake Holiday, Plano, Hinckley, Sandwich, and Somonauk
around 210 PM CDT.
North Aurora around 215 PM CDT.
Geneva, Yorkville, Montgomery, Aurora, and Batavia around 220 PM
CDT.
Oswego around 225 PM CDT.
Boulder Hill and West Chicago around 230 PM CDT.
Plainfield around 240 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include
Millbrook, Kaneville, Millington, Little Rock, Big Rock, and Bristol.

Including the following interstate...
I-88 between mile markers 107 and 120.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
